        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 4:24PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 424 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sugarbowl Ski Resort, or near Soda Springs, moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cisco, Kingvale, and Sugarbowl Ski Resort.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
